Summary of Position<br>
<br>
Responsible for the operation of the food services program and preparation of family style meals for residents and employees.<br>
<br>
Essential Functions<br>
  <br>
•	Demonstrates a clear understanding of the Covenant House Mission, philosophy, history and tradition(s) and the underlying values upon which the Agency is founded to the staff, youth and the community we serve<br>
•	Understand and comply with all Agency policies and procedures.<br>
•	Maintain a high level of ethical standards.<br>
•	Ensure the safety of youth seen by CHA at all times.<br>
•	Supervise daily operation of the food services staff<br>
•	In conjunction with the Director, interview, hire, evaluate, and discipline food services staff.<br>
•	Establish standards and procedures, as approved by the Director, for food services staff, volunteers or contractors.<br>
•	Plan work schedules to ensure adequate services are provided.<br>
•	Ensure that all food service areas to meet and exceed State Health guidelines relating to sanitation and safety inspections.<br>
•	Maintaining accurate records of food disbursements, ordering, and stocking in accordance with SOA/USDA program requirements.<br>
•	Ensure that all food is prepared and served in accordance with the state nutrition guidelines as set forth in the "Alaska School Food Service Manual"<br>
•	Ensure that food orders are placed on a timely basis in accordance with agency purchasing policy<br>
•	Prepare meals based on approved cycle menu and number of anticipated individuals to be served in a cost effective and efficient manner.<br>
•	Ensure that donations, food bank, and other supplies are received and used in the safest and most productive manner.<br>
•	Maintain all food service equipment in a clean and safe manner.<br>
•	Coordinate special events requiring food services support, by ordering, contracting, or other means needed.<br>
•	Manage and prepare in-house catering for agency meetings and events<br>
•	Provide informal training in cooking and safe food handling to staff and residents as needed<br>
•	Ability to work independently, using good judgment, and common sense<br>
•	Keep supervisor fully informed at all times<br>
•	Others duties as assigned<br>
<br>
Minimum Education<br>
High school graduate. Post-secondary food service training desirable. Must possess a Municipal food handlers certification or equivalent, a vocational degree is preferred.<br>
<br>
Minimum Experience<br>
Minimum of 2 years of food services management including supervision of employees and volunteers.  Must have 2-3 years' experience either in institutional or commercial cooking.  Familiarity with cycle menu planning management.  Experience with SOA food service programs preferred.<br>
<br>
Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities Required<br>
<br>
•	Knowledge of cycle menu planning.<br>
•	Demonstrated ability to communicate with adolescents in a direct, non-threatening manner.<br>
•	Knowledge of maintaining food service budgets, supplies and inventories<br>
•	Possess a Municipal food handlers certification or equivalent<br>
•	Ability to prioritize multiple tasks <br>
•	Good customer service skills <br>
•	Basic understanding of adolescent development and behaviors; demonstrate enjoyment of and ability to relate to at-risk youth and demonstrates empathy with the joys and pains of others<br>
•	Strong ability to relate effectively with staff, youth, and community agencies; <br>
•	Is approachable, builds rapport well and practices attentive and active listening.<br>
•	Ability to address conflict well and manage difficult youth in a supportive, non-threatening manner; Able to respond quickly and safely and is a settling influence in crisis situations and emergencies<br>
•	Ability to work with people of varied cultural backgrounds and tolerate differences in behavior.<br>
•	Support equal and fair treatment and opportunity for all; tolerant of people and processes.<br>
•	Ability to work independently, using good judgment, and common sense<br>
•	Able to make good decisions consistently based upon a mixture of analysis, wisdom, experience and judgment. <br>
•	Maintain confidentiality and presents the straightforward truth<br>
•	Self-motivation, initiative, sound judgment, and commitment to ongoing learning are essential<br>
•	Proficient with standard computer operating systems;<br>
•	Excellent oral and written, communication skills including organizational skills;  <br>
•	Willingness and ability to work outside of normal business hours, and Holidays and/or weekends as needed.<br>
•	Able to physically accommodate a wide range of strenuous physical activity, including but not limited to walking long distances, moving up and down stairs, lift bags/boxes up to 50 pounds, drive a minivan and physically manage youth if needed<br>
•	Possess a current state of Alaska Driving License <br>
•	Have a clean driving record<br>
•	Pass federal, state and local background investigation<br>
<br>
Please visit our website to apply - <a href="http://ak.covenanthouse.org/Employment-opportunities" rel="nofollow">http://ak.covenanthouse.org/Employment-opportunities</a> <br>
<br>
Submit your application, resume, cover letter, and list of references to the attention of:<br>
Human Resources Generalist, Covenant House Alaska <br>
<br>
Covenant House is an Equal Opportunity Employer<br>
